<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 2 - Active mana regeneration</b><br />
<br />
Just about anything a shaman can do seems to have been designed with cannibalize in mind. Whenever a shaman complains about any of his abilities one of the arguments invariably is "but you can cannibalize" (the other being "but you have slow").<br />
<br />
Cannibalize does have a major problem though. As noted above cannibalize os one of our mutually exclusive abilities. While we are cannibalizing we are not doing anything else. This used to be no problem at all back in Kunark - back then med breaks were common, every caster conserved their mana and cast spells sparingly, giving shaman the time to cannibalize without falling behind.<br />
<br />
Apparently this was deemed to powerful and every shaman spell since Kunark is, compared to the upgrades other casters got, more expensive as well as slower casting and has a lesser effect.<br />
<br />
Fast forward to today. Whereas a healer used to be expected to cast a heal or two every minute they are now required to spend half of their time casting. Similar things are expected of the damage classes.<br />
Now, given slower casting times and lesser effects a shaman will easily spend not 50% but 80% of his time casting these spells and still pay more mana for them. He now has little time left to cannibalize the additional mana back.<br />
<br />
This not only puts the shaman on par or below over long durations, it also means that shaman burst healing or damage capabilities are much less then other classes' abilities - and burst healing and burst DPS are becoming more and more critical in the last expansions.<br />
<br />
This is part two of the shaman problem. We simply do not have enough time to use our active mana regeneration if we want to match or even come close to other classes' capabilities.<br />
<br />
______________________________<br />
<b>numbers for the above</b><br />
<br />
At first glance shaman mana regeneration seems impressive.<br />
Cannibalize IV will bring back 82 mana every 5.5 seconds.<br />
In addition the cannibalisation skill will generate 1066 mana every 3 minutes.<br />
This adds up to a total 3712 mana every 3 minutes, or 124 mana per tick<br />
<br />
Druids on the other hand only regain 12 mana per tick (Blessing of the 9 + Mask of the Forest).<br />
<br />
Now let me show you a scenario - we will compare sustained shaman nuking to a druid's. I chose nukes for my comparison because the druid DoT spells have a resist modifier, which is hard to account for.<br />
<br />
Both the shaman and the druid will have a mana preservation item (10% average), an improved damage item (10% average) , a spell haste item (10% fixed), flowing thought 15,  and mental clarity 3. Both will use a horse. In addition the shaman has the cannibalisation AA.<br />
Both will be buffed with Blessing of the 9, Voice of Quellious and Spiritual Dominion. In addition the druid will be buffed with Mask of the Forest.<br />
I will assume assume neither shaman nor druid are specialized in evocation (thus a 3% mana saving on all spells).<br />
<br />
To account for the nature of cannibalizing I will first compute the shaman mana regeneration as if he was doing nothing but generate mana and then add to the cost of each spell he casts the mana he could have generated in that time.<br />
<br />
<b>Shaman mana regeneration:</b><br />
One cast of breath of Trushar costs 285 mana and heals 4*360 =1440 damage.<br />
Focused mana cost is 214.<br />
That is enough damage healed to offset 9.7 casts of cannibalize IV.<br />
One of these cycles generates (9.7*82)-214=583 mana and takes (9.7*4.75)+7.95=54.2 seconds.<br />
Shaman mana regeneration from cannibalize IV is thus 10.8 mana per second or 65 mana per tick.<br />
<br />
The cannibalisation AA will bring back 1066 mana at the cost of 1924 damage. Healing this damage with Breath of Trushar takes 1.34 casts, which costs 287 mana. The total mana generated by one cycle of cannibalisation is 779 every 3 minutes, or 26 mana per tick.<br />
<br />
The shaman's mana regeneration over 3 minutes is thus 779 (from cannibalisation) + 1909 (from 177.5/54.2=3.27 cycles of cannibalize IV) = 2688 mana every 3 minutes, or <b>90 mana per tick</b> (14.93 mana per second).<br />
<br />
Now, this was the mana from cannibalizing - added to this is the mana from the above sources (same for druid and shaman).<br />
<br />
28 (meditation mana at lvl 65) + 8 (Blessing of the 9) + 18 (Voice of Quellious) + 9 (Spiritual Dominion) + 15 (Flowing thought) + 3 (Mental Clarity) + 4 (Mask of the Forest; druid only).<br />
<br />
This brings total mana regeneration per tick to<br />
171 (shaman)<br />
85 (druid)<br />
<br />
Now let us compare the nuke spells available to both classes.<br />
<br />
The shaman will be using Velium Strike.<br />
Velium Strike does 925 damage every 10.05 seconds. Accounting for focuses and specialisation brings this to 925*1.1=1018 damage every (7.8*0.9)+2.25=9.3 seconds for 300*0.87=261 mana. We do also lose 9.3 seconds worth of cannibalize mana, which amounts to a total mana cost of 400.<br />
A shaman can thus cast Velium Strike every 400/171=2.3 ticks, or every 14 seconds, which amounts to 1018/14=<b>72.9 DPS</b>.<br />
The shaman's burst DPS is 1018/9.3=<b>109 DPS</b>.<br />
<br />
The druid will be casting Sylvan Fire.<br />
Sylvan Fire does 1705 damage for 430 mana every 9 seconds. The numbers adjusted for focuses are 1705*1.1=1876 damage for 430*0.87=374 mana every (6.75*0.9)+2.25=8.3 seconds.<br />
A druid can thus cast Sylvan Fire every 374/85=4.4 ticks, or every 26 seconds, which amounts to 1876/26=<b>72.2 DPS</b>.<br />
The druid's burst DPS is 1876/8.3=<b>226 DPS</b>.<br />
<br />
Now, this is over an infinite timespan. If we instead allow for a med break every 20 minutes both the druid and the shaman can also empty their mana pool.<br />
A mana pool of 6000 mana emptied over 20 minutes amount to another 30 mana per tick.<br />
<br />
With this extra mana the shaman damage rises to 1018 every 400/191=2.1 ticks for a DPS of 1018/(2.1*6)=<b>81.3 DPS</b>.<br />
The druid damage rises to 1876 every 374/115=3.3 ticks for a DPS of 1876/(3.3*6)=<b>96.1 DPS</b>.<br />
<br />
So even chainnuking for 20 minutes straight the shaman does not match druid nuking damage. Chainnuking for literally an eternity the shaman pulls ahead of the druid by less then a percent.<br />
<br />
Note that this shaman has no lag at all, does not stop casting for even a quarter of a second, never overheals his cannibalize damage and never fizzles. He also magically finds something to cast in the 0.75 seconds between casting cannibalize IV and the cannibalize IV gem refreshing and he never moves.<br />
The druid on the other hand is only casting 30% of the time and thus has ample time to move or make up for lag or fizzles.<br />
<br />
Neither character is using resists debuffs - this would skew the results further in favor of the druid due to their cheap and fast fire debuff line.</p>
	
	
	
	
