<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 4 - Casting times &amp; Impact</b><br />
<br />
The obvious general spell design for a class with active mana regeneration would have been expensive but fast casting spells so as to leave time to make up for the mana. Shaman spells however are slow, inefficient and have a lesser effect then comparable spells of other classes.<br />
<br />
Shaman are thus simply unable to match the short term damage or healing output of other classes. These days "short term" might as well be defined as "anything under 5 minutes". That is the point where other classes might start to go out of mana. It does not mean a shaman starts to overtake a cleric's healing or a necromancer's damage. This is where a shaman starts to catch up. With the inefficient and low impact spells shaman get catching up to either over any length of time is simply impossible.<br />
<br />
This is part four of the shaman problem. Slow casting times and low impact spells prevent us from matching anyone at all in the short term and from ever catching up to the top classes in the long term.<br />
At best we can hope to catch the secondary healers or secondary damage dealers in the long term - however these long term fights do not exist anymore.<br />
<br />
<br />
_________________<br />
<b>healing numbers</b><br />
<br />
I will compare the nuking and healing capabilities of the priest classes over 1 minute, 2 minutes and 5 minutes. The comparison will look at single targets heals only, as druids and shaman do not have group heals.<br />
I will also list paladin capabilities for the one minute period - I do not know where meditation caps for paladins so any long term numbers would be off (though certainly behind shaman numbers due to their inefficient single target heals).<br />
<br />
I will be using the same numbers for this scenario as above (10% average focus items for heals, nukes, mana preservation and spell haste, specialisation: alteration for all classes.). The mana regeneration for the classes is:<br />
<b>174</b> (shaman)<br />
<b> 85</b> (druid)<br />
<b> 81</b> (cleric)<br />
(for details see above)<br />
<br />
The shaman will be using these heals:<br />
<u>Tnarg's Mending</u><br />
1430 HPs healed in 5.6 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 422.<br />
<br />
<u>Breath of Trushar</u><br />
1440 HPs healed in over 24 seconds with a cast time of 7.7 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 331.<br />
<i>(for the concept of adjusted mana cost see above)</i><br />
<br />
The druid will be using these heals:<br />
<u>Karana's Renewal</u><br />
4680 HPs healed in 12.25 seconds with a mana cost of 510.<br />
<br />
<u>Sylvan Infusion</u><br />
2310 HPs healed in 5.6 seconds with a mana cost of 375.<br />
<br />
The cleric will be using these heals (I will assume CH lands for 5K):<br />
<u>Complete Healing</u><br />
5000 HPs healed in 12.25 seconds with a mana cost of 340.<br />
<br />
<u>Holy Light</u><br />
3603 HPs healed in 5.6 seconds with a mana cost of 488.<br />
<br />
The paladin will be using these heals<br />
<u>Light of Order</u><br />
1100 HPs healed in 3.25 seconds with a mana cost of 387.<br />
<br />
<u>Light of Nife</u><br />
935 HPs healed in 3.25 seconds with a mana cost of 360.<br />
<br />
<u>Light of Order + Light of Nife</u><br />
2035 HPs healed in 6.5 seconds with a mana cost of 747.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><u>1 minute:</u></b><br />
<b>Shaman:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*171(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 7710<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Tnarg's Mending 60/5.6= 10.71 times for a total of 10.71*1430= <b>15315 HPs healed</b> with 3190 mana left over.<br />
<br />
<b>Druid:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*85(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 6850<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Sylvan Infusion 60/5.6= 10.71 times for a total of 10.71*2310= <b>24740</b> HPs healed with 2834 mana left over.<br />
<br />
<b>Cleric</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*81(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 6810<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Holy Light 60/5.6= 10.71 times for a total of 10.71*3603= <b>35932 HPs healed</b> with 1584 mana left over.<br />
<br />
<b>Paladin</b><br />
Total mana to spend = unknown - I am going to assume it is enuff for 1 minute of alternating Light of Nife and Light of Order<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Light of Nife + Light of Order 60/6.5= 9.23 times for a total of 9.23*2305= <b>21275 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><u>2 minutes:</u></b><br />
<b>Shaman:</b><br />
The shaman is not running out of mana yet thus he heals double the above amount for a total <b>30630 HPs healed</b><br />
<br />
<b>Druid:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 20*85(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 7700<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast Karana's Renewal 3 times and Sylvan Infusion 6170/375= 16.45 times for a total (4680*3)+(2310*16.45)= <b>52040 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Cleric</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 20*81(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 7620<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast Complete Healing 3.5 times and Holy Light 6430/488=13.18 times for a total (5000*3.5)+(3603*13.18)=<b>64988 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><u>5 minutes:</u></b><br />
<b>Shaman:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*171(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 14550<br />
<br />
Keeping up Trushar is 300/24= 12.5 casts of Trushar for 12.5*331= 4138 mana. That leaves 10412 mana for 10412/422= 24.67 casts of Tnarg's Mending.<br />
This will heal a total of (12.5*1440)+(24.67*1430)=<b>53278 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Druid:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*85(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 10250<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast Karana's Renewal 10250/510= 20.1 times for a total 4680*20.1= <b>94068 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Cleric</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*81(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 10050<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast Complete Healing 22 times and Holy Light 2570/488= 5.27 times for a total (5000*22)+(3603*5.27)=<b>128988 HPs healed</b>.<br />
<br />
<br />
Looking at the numbers it is clear that shaman cannot come close to druid or cleric healing in anything remotely resembling a short fight. We actually do comparatively better in 1 minute fights as the various spot heals are not as far apart as Tnarg's is to the percentage heals.<br />
<br />
Furthermore paladins easily outheal us in the spot heal department.<br />
<br />
Note that a cleric can, with group buffs, keep chaincasting complete heal for more then 6 minutes before going out of mana. Also it takes the shaman a 65% slow to keep up with the cleric, assuming said slow is never resisted, does not draw aggro, is not mitigated, casts instantly and costs 0 mana.<br />
<br />
This is over a 5 minute fight (and holds true for a fight duration of up to 8 minutes - after that a shaman starts to make up ground). Even given infinite fight length a shaman will never catch up to a cleric and it takes well in excess of half an hour of fighting to catch up to a druid.<br />
<br />
_________________<br />
<b>nuking numbers</b><br />
<br />
<br />
The shaman will be using<br />
<u>Velium Strike</u><br />
1018 damage in 9.3 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 401.<br />
(for the concept of adjusted mana cost see above)<br />
<br />
The druid will be using<br />
<u>Sylvan Fire</u><br />
1876 damage in 8.4 seconds with a mana cost of 387.<br />
<br />
The cleric will be using his 2 best nukes, as the recast on them is pretty long.<br />
<u>Order</u><br />
1331 damage in 8.1 seconds with a mana cost of 349.<br />
<br />
<u>Condemnation</u><br />
1210 damage in 8.1 seconds with a mana cost of 318.<br />
<br />
<u>Order + Condemnation</u><br />
2541 damage in 16.2 seconds with a mana cost of 668.<br />
<br />
<b><u>1 minute:</u></b><br />
<b>Shaman:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*171(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 7710<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Velium Strike 60/9.3= 6.45 times for a total of 6.45*1018= <b>6566 damage</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Druid:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*85(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 6850<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Sylvan Fire 60/8.4= 7.14 times for a total of 7.14*1876= <b>13395 damage</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Cleric</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 10*81(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 6810<br />
<br />
60 seconds is enough time to cast Order+Condemnation 60/16.2= 3.7 times for a total of 3.7*2541= <b>9402 damage</b>.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><u>2 minutes:</u></b><br />
Noone will run out of mana yet, so just double the above numbers.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><u>5 minutes:</u></b><br />
<b>Shaman:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*171(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 14550<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast 14550/401=36.28 casts of Velium Strike for a total damage of 36.28*1018=<b>36933 damage</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Druid:</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*85(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 10250<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast 10250/387=26.49 casts of Sylvan Fire for a total damage of 26.49*1876=<b>49695 damage</b>. Time spent casting is 26.49*8.4=222.5 seconds.<br />
<br />
<b>Cleric</b><br />
Total mana to spend = 50*81(mana regeneration) + 6000(mana pool) = 10050<br />
<br />
This is enough to cast 10050/668=15.04 casts of Order+Condemnation for a total damage of 15.04*2541=<b>38217 damage</b>. Time spent casting is x*16.2=243.6 seconds.<br />
<br />
<br />
As you can see shaman are dead last in the fast damage category. Simply put, mana regeneration and mana pools have increased to the point where noone is running out of mana on a single fight, even if it involves multiple MOBs.<br />
As shaman nukes are slower and smaller then comparable nukes of other classes there is simply no way to catch up to anyone in the short term, and it takes way longer then any single fight to match even a cleric.<br />
Note that the shaman is rooted to spot, while the 5 minute numbers leave the cleric and druid ample time to move (and the druid has a 0.5 second window each nuke to move in due to recast).</p>
	
	
	
	
