<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 6 - Fast fights &amp; constant movement</b><br />
<br />
Planes of Power introduced MOBs with huge damage output and comparatively very low HPs. Lost Dungeons introduced the concept of constant movement.<br />
<br />
Neither of these concepts are bad per se. Both do however reduce the effectiveness of the shaman.<br />
<br />
Short fights mean that the contribution of slow is lessened. If a MOB spends 90% of the fight slowed the overall slow percentage will be very close to the maximum value of 75%. If however the MOB spends a third of the fight unslowed this overall slow percentage drops to 50%. As the corresponding MOB damage output is 25% and 50% this means that the effectiveness of slow is halved.<br />
<br />
Constant movement simply means less time for a shaman to cannibalize. Everyone looses mana by moving, but buffs still provide their mana regeneration while the extra mana from cannibalize that the shaman was balanced around is lessened.<br />
<br />
This is part six of the shaman problem. The short brutal fights and constant movement of GoD (and to a lesser extent the previous expansions), while not a bad thing by itself, indirectly nerf key shaman abilities.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=d24e53c4460b51e7593cc756a8bdee5c&amp;postid=231866">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=d24e53c4460b51e7593cc756a8bdee5c&amp;do=getip&postid=231866">Logged</a></div>
	
