	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 7 - Slow mitigation</b><br />
<br />
Slow is also adversely affected by another thing - slow mitigation. Slow mitigation lessens the percentage by which a MOB is slowed. Due to the way slow works the scaling is a little curious however.<br />
Reducing a slow by a third from 75% to 50% halves its effectiveness.<br />
Reducing a slow by two thirds from 75% to 25% quarters its effectiveness.<br />
Reducing a slow by half from 50% to 25% halves its effectiveness.<br />
<br />
Generally speaking, those last couple percent of slow (from 50 to 75 %) are the most effective and are the first to go when slow mitigation is applied.<br />
<br />
Even a small mitigation in slow effectiveness of a quarter of the original value gets very close to halving the effectiveness of shaman slow. Just reducing the slow percentage of a shaman by a tenth reduces the slowing power by 30%.<br />
<br />
Bards, beastlords and enchanters, though similarly affected, experience a lesser reduction in the effectiveness of their slows.<br />
<br />
This is part seven of the shaman problem. Slow mitigation, even the least variations of it, have a huge impact on the effectiveness of slow. As slow is the only contribution to a group that shaman are clearly best at this greatly reduces the overall shaman contribution.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
