<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 8 - Shaman healing &amp; slow</b><br />
<br />
Shaman healing seems to have been designed with slow in mind. That is, a shaman would be able to keep his group alive after he slowed the MOB.<br />
<br />
Aside from the obvious problems - MOBs generally do not arrive slowed, adds have to be slowed separately, spell and riposte damage is not lessened by slow - this might well have been true during the Luclin era.<br />
<br />
Nowadays however, even on non-mitigating MOBs, the short fight durations reduce the effectiveness of slow a lot. On the other hand the comparatively greater increases to cleric and druid mana regeneration compared the tiny increases shaman got mean that we have more healing to do then we used to so we can match a cleric's or druid's overall healing.<br />
However we have to do this with spells that cast slower, heal less and take more mana.<br />
<br />
In GoD another problem has become apparent. It is very possible that a shaman can just barely keep up with an unslowed MOB by chaincasting heal. That means that in the case of a resisted slow the tank will need chain healing, leaving no time for a new try at slowing.<br />
<br />
Druid or cleric healing does not have this problem, as their heals were not designed with a resistable spell in mind.<br />
<br />
This situation of course does not get better when you take into account slow mitigation or flat out slow immune MOBs.<br />
<br />
This is part eight of the shaman problem. Our healing was designed with slow and our superior mana regeneration in mind. Neither of these applies to the degree it used to and this is if we even get a chance to use any of it. Even if we can slow a MOB decently we barely break even with other healers and are much much worse when emergency healing is needed (such as in the case of an add).<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
_________________________<br />
<b>a healing scenario</b><br />
<br />
This scenario will compare the healing capabilities of the classes over a timeframe of 30 minutes in a static camp with non-mitigating MOBs who last 1 minute each. Pull time between MOBs is 5 seconds. MOBs will not resist slow once Malos has been cast.<br />
<br />
Reposted numbers from above:<br />
Mana regeneration:<br />
171 (shaman) for a total mana of 57300.<br />
 85 (druid) for a total mana of 31500.<br />
 81 (cleric) for a total mana of 30300.<br />
<br />
The shaman will be using<br />
<u>Tnarg's Mending</u><br />
1430 HPs healed in 5.6 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 422.<br />
<br />
<u>Breath of Trushar</u><br />
1440 HPs healed in over 24 seconds with a cast time of 7.7 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 331.<br />
<br />
<u>Turgur's Insects</u><br />
Slows by 75% in 4.95 seconds (2.7 seconds until slow hits) with an adjusted mana cost of 262.<br />
<br />
<u>Malos</u><br />
Debuffs by 55 in 6.75 seconds with an adjusted mana cost of 401.<br />
<br />
<br />
The druid will be using<br />
<u>Karana's Renewal</u><br />
4680 HPs healed in 12.25 seconds with a mana cost of 510.<br />
<br />
<br />
The cleric will be using<br />
<u>Complete Healing</u><br />
5000 HPs healed in 12.25 seconds with a mana cost of 340.<br />
<br />
<br />
The shaman will be keeping up Trushar. 1800/24=75 casts of Trushar, leaving 57300-(331*75)=32475 mana for slowing and using Tnarg's. Malos/Turgur's will have to be cast 1800/65=27.69 times. Each such debuff cycle uses 262+401=663 mana and slows for 1-((100%*9.45 + 25%*50.65)/60)=63% overall.<br />
This leaves us with 32475-(27.69*663)=14117 mana for Tnarg's. 14117/501=33.45 casts for a total healing of (33.45*1430)+(75*1440)=155836 HPs healed. Accounting for slow this means (155836/(1-63%))/1800= <b>234 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
The cleric casts Complete Healing 30300/340=89.12 times for a total healing of 446000 meaning 446000/1800= <b>247.8 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
The druid casts Karana's Renewal 31500/510=61.76 times for a total healing of 289037 meaning 289037/1800= <b>160.6 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
<br />
So, on long fights, fighting nonstop for 30 minutes our hypothetical shaman outheals a druid and is still outhealed by a cleric(who does not has a slower in the group), even on nonmitigating MOBs. Lets see what short fights, slow mitigation and movement do for the classes.<br />
<br />
The scenario remains unchanged except for:<br />
- MOBs last 30 seconds<br />
- after every kill the group will move for 5 seconds instead of pulling for 5 seconds.<br />
- MOBs mitigate slow by 25% to 56.25%.<br />
<br />
Moving for a total of 1800/35*5=257.1 seconds reduces the available mana by the cannibalize/meditation mana to:<br />
Shaman 57300-(257.1*129/6) = 51972 mana<br />
Druid 31500-(257.1*28/6) = 30300 mana<br />
Cleric 30300-(257.1*28/6) = 29100 mana<br />
<br />
The shaman will now have to debuff 1800/35=51.43 times leaving 51962-(51.43*663)=17864 mana for actual healing. That is enough for 17864/331=53.97 casts of Trushar for a total healing of 53.97*1440=77716 HPs healed. Due to slow mitigation we will have to recalculate the slow percentage: 1-((100%*9.45 + 56.25%*20.65)/30)=30% overall.<br />
Our total damage mitigation is thus (37771/(1-30%))/1800= <b>61.7 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
Now, clearly it is not worth casting slow under these circumstances. So the shaman will just heal instead. Keeping up Trushar takes 75 casts, leaving 51962-(75*331)=27137 mana for Tnargs. This is 27137/422=64.3 casts of Tnarg's for a total healing of (75*1440)+(64.3*1430)= 199950 HPs healed and 199950/1800= <b>111.1 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
The cleric casts Complete Healing 29100/340=85.59 times for a total healing of 427950 meaning 427950/1800= <b>237.8 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
The druid casts Karana's Renewal 30300/510=59.41 times for a total healing of 278039 meaning 278039/1800= <b>154.5 DPS negated</b>.<br />
<br />
On the type of fight prevalent in LDoN and GoD it is not even worth to cast slow unless you have several other healers in the group. Even over extended periods of nonstop fighting we still heal less then a druid and clerics outheal us by a factor of more then two.<br />
This does not take into account that the shaman healing is mainly coming from HoT spells, which, while efficient, are far too slow to keep a tank alive in GoD or even in a hard LDoN adventure. Also these spells do not stack, whereas cleric and druid heals have no such issues.<br />
Note that a few seconds of moving, the lowest level of slow mitigation and 30 second fights reduce a shaman's healing capabilities by 53%, while only reducing cleric and druid healing by 4% and 3.8% respectively.</p>
	
	
	
	
