	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Part 9 - Nothing new for the shaman</b><br />
<br />
Shaman have literally not gotten a new spell line since Kunark. The closest thing to a new spell line is the Bane line from LDoN - which is just another DoT, albeit with a different resist. We have gotten upgrades to existing spell lines, and smaller upgrades then any other class at that.<br />
<br />
Lets take a look at the other classes shaman compete with in certain areas. I am going from memory here so I might well miss something.<br />
Shaman - bearform<br />
Cleric - spell haste line. pacify line. hammer line. vie line. self buff line.<br />
Druid - mana regeneration added to the skin line. various debuff lines.<br />
Enchanter - spell damage rune. side effects removed from nuke line.<br />
Necromancer - group lifetaps. group mana taps.<br />
(Beastlord - entire class is new)<br />
Paladin - unique HP buff line. self buff line. group heals.<br />
<br />
Overall shaman have not only gotten the least upgrades to their existing spell lines, they also got the fewest and least useful new spell lines.<br />
<br />
This is part 9 of the shaman problem. We have now gotten the least upgrades of all classes who can cast spells from six expansions straight and it shows. In addition every new ability implemented went to other classes.<br />
<br />
<br />
____________________<br />
<b>spell increases since Kunark</b><br />
<br />
I will compare the increases to various shaman spell lines and similar spell lines of other classes from Kunark until PoP. As I am interested in increases the total values are of less interest to me then the percentage of the increase.<blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Hitpoint buffs     Kunark    PoP     % increase
Shaman              395       544    + 38%
Druid               415       618    + 49%
Cleric             1125      1430    + 27%
Paladin             775      1455    + 88%
Ranger              325       540    + 66%
Beastlord             -       620       -
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>average increase 54%</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Haste/ATK    Kunark    PoP    % increase
Shaman       60        76      +  27%
Enchanter    70        77      +  10%
Bard         45        93      + 107%
Beastlord    -        69           -
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>average increase 48%</b><br />
<i>(in haste %, counting 10ATK as 1% haste. Additional ATK on bard songs due to intrument modifiers is not calculated.)</i><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Slowing      Kunark    PoP    % increase
Shaman       75      75      +   0%
Enchanter    70      70      +   0%
Bard         23      52      + 126%
Beastlord     -      65           -
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>average increase 42%</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Resist Debuffs     Kunark     PoP     % increase
Shaman            60      70      + 17%
Magician          60      70      + 17%
Enchanter         41      50      + 22%
Necromancer       36      36      +  0%
Druid           33      97      +194%
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>average increase 50%</b><br />
<br />
<br />
Heals have been covered in detail above, as well as the relationship between heals and slows.<br />
<br />
<br />
The following are straight reposts from an older post of mine. They are accurate for Kunark to PoP but to not yet account for GoD spells.<br />
<br />
<b>DoT efficiency</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Shaman
 - Poison           4.0     5.1         +  28%
 - Disease          5.0     7.3         +  46%
Necromancer
 - Lifedrain        2.3     4.8         + 109%
 - Fire             5.1     6.9         +  35%
 - Poison           3.7     5.7         +  54%
 - Snare            4.1     8.5         + 107%
Druid
 - Ro               4.1     5.3         + 29%
 - Swarm            4.1     4.7         + 15%
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>DoT damage per second</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Shaman
 - Poison           33.5    45.5        +  36%
 - Disease          18.1    20.8        +  15%
Necromancer
 - Lifedrain        17.8    29.6        +  66%
 - Fire             17.3    38.4        + 122%
 - Poison           22.5    48.5        + 116%
 - Snare            18.5    11.2        -  39%
Druid
 - Ro               14.0    23.5        +  68%
 - Swarm            21.5    33.0        +  53%
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>Nuke efficiency</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Shaman              2.8     3.5     +  25%
Cleric              2.7     3.7     +  37%
Druid               3.7     4.8     +  30%
Wizard              4.0     5.7     +  43%
Enchanter           3.2     4.2     +  31%
Necromancer         2.0     5.6     + 180%
Magician            3.4     5.2     +  53%
Ranger              1.7     2.6     +  53%
<hr /></pre></blockquote><b>Nuke damage per second</b><blockquote><pre>Code:<hr />
Shaman               73     100     +  37%
Cleric               86     136     +  58%
Druid               136     195     +  43%
Wizard              175     290     +  66%
Enchanter            94     144     +  53%
Necromancer          87     170     +  95%
Magician            111     195     +  76%
Ranger               73     164     + 125%
<hr /></pre></blockquote></p>
	
	
	
	
