<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Conclusions</b><br />
<br />
Shaman feel neglected due to a variety of reasons. We have not gotten the same amount of upgrades to our spell lines as everyone else did. Our existing abilities have been nerfed directly (slow mitigation) and indirectly (fast fights) to a point where many of us feel that we no longer adequately contribute to a group, much less a raid. Our key abilities, slow and mana regeneration are no longer as useful as they once were and we received nothing new to make up for it. Our healing is arguably weaker then a paladin's, our buffing is arguably weaker then a beastlord's, our damage is pathetic.<br />
Basically there is not much left of a class many of us have grown to love. We would like to once more feel like we contribute to a group. As is, I have not been in a group in months where I could not have been replaced by someone better suited for the group.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
