<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>What to do now?</b><br />
Shaman have been neglected for so long that we need help in a lot of areas. I will try to tailor my proposals so they are useful for fixing the current shaman issues as well as helping provide a role on raids.<br />
<br />
<b>Healing</b><br />
Shaman need a better patch heal, both for raids, backup healing and (on easier content) to be able to recover from slow resists when main healing. The following are all options for patch heals.<br />
<br />
<u>Tnarg's Improved Mending</u><br />
610 mana, 3.5 cast time, 2.25 refresh, heals 1800 HPs<br />
<br />
<u>Spirit Shifting</u><br />
AA ability in 3 tiers for 4/4/4 points. Creates a hotkey with a 0.5 second cast time and 1 minute reuse time that damages the shaman by 20/30/40 % of his current HPs and heals an equal amount of damage to the target.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Damage</b><br />
Shaman damage is not only largely useless (DoTs) or horribly underpowered (nukes), we also cannot keep up with any class remotely resembling a damage class (i.e. druids) even on long (20 minutes and longer) fights, which is supposed to be a shaman strength. In addition, one of our supposed strengths, DoT spells, do not have the favorable resist adjustments druids and necromancers have.<br />
These are some options to increase shaman damage.<br />
<br />
<u>Winter Spirit</u><br />
400 mana, 6 second cast time, 2.25 refresh, does 1250 cold damage.<br />
<br />
<u>Doom</u><br />
same stats as Bane, except change resist adjustment to -100.<br />
<br />
<u>Venom Strike</u><br />
330 mana, 5 second cast time, 2.25 refresh, does 1000 poison damage.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Buffs</b><br />
Shaman buffs not only have received less upgrades then other classes' buff lines but also had their stat buff parts rendered useless due to stat caps. Hence shaman require a slight upgrade to their non-stat buffs and a replacement of the stat buffs to be brought back in line with other classes.<br />
<br />
<u>Focus of the Heyokah</u><br />
same stats as Focus of the 7th except<br />
- increase HPs to 600<br />
- replace stat adjustments with 3% DoT shielding, spell shielding and shielding.<br />
<br />
<u>Kragg's Avatar</u><br />
1200 mana, group buff (not /TGBable), lasts 20 minutes.<br />
140 ATK, +20 strikethrough, accuracy, combat effects<br />
<br />
<u>Talisman of Swiftness</u><br />
same stats as Talisman of Alacrity except increase haste % to 60% (same as Swift like the Wind)<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Debuffs</b><br />
The defining class ability of the shaman, slow, has not been upgraded since Kunark, yet other classes now slow within a couple percent of our best slow. As the slow percentage on Turgur's is as good as the game design allows it any upgrades will have to come in other areas.<br />
Resist and stat debuffs have been largely static for everyone (and are a far less integral part of the shaman class), so no adjustment are needed there.<br />
<br />
<u>Teger's Insects</u><br />
280 mana, 3.0 second cast time, 2.25 second recast time, -40 resist adjustment, 75% slow, 7 minute duration<br />
<br />
I am not sure if the above is enough to rebalance shaman to the current content but it should be enough to balance shaman against the other classes. Depending on how much GoD encounters get retuned it may at least be enough to not make us shaman feel useless in the short fights of the last 3 expansions.</p>
	
	
	
	
