	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Very nicely done. I can only disagree with one of your points, and that is that Shaman cannot be effective healers in "much" of the content. This is simply not the case. It is ONLY this newer content that Shamans healing effectiveness is severly limited. I can still effectively do my duties (Malos, Slow, Heal group) in 90% of the games content, even in XP groups in the EPs. <br />
<br />
The rest I agree with wholeheartedly. <br />
<br />
Solutions: Once again, I will say how I feel. A slight bump to our fastest heal and nuke (a 1600-1800 fast heal, a 1K fast nuke) and I think we will be effective again. IF, and I say this with some reservation, IF they are going to change BoT to 460 a tic, that would be wonderful, and added the changes I have suggested, it would make us "whole" again. <br />
<br />
The game has become more of a "how fast can you . . ." type of play than the grind we have been used to for years. How fast can you kill 50 things? How fast can you kill this mob that is quadding for 1200? How fast can you kill these 4 that all charge? This change in focus toward speed is what is killing us, cause our "fastest" spells just arent cutting it.</p>
	
	
	
