	<p>great post to begin with btw. I agree with alot of what you say it's all is pretty much dead on. I assume your on a blue server only because there is no mention of pvp so i'll toss my 2 cents in about that.<br />
<br />
A year ago b4 everyone had tons of elemental/time gear i could go into a fight 1 on 1 with just about any class and kill them in pvp. now i find it hard to kill anyone. No changes to resist checks on spells I or any shaman uses in PVP alot have been made and 95% of my stuff gets resisted. Albeit i'm damn near unkillable with Breath of trushar and the gear i have but the lack of KS's in pvp i get now have taken alot away from game for me. With everyones HP and resists getting better daily our DPS hasn't gotten better at all. jeez i first heard about Bane when ldon was coming out and was praying for something that would land pvp. instead they gave us a DoT that takes forever to pop when memmed and has a huge recast time. so it gets resisted and i have to wait to try it again. As far as pvp with this spell well there isn't any. It's 100% useless in pvp cause anyone with 200mr will resist it 100% of the time and anyone that i could otherwise land it on newbiewise will die fast enough that it's a waste of time to mem it. Evereyones toons get better and better as time goes on and ppl get mreo aa's and we just get absolutely nothing pvp wise to counter this. every other class pretty much gets upgrades. Druids got swarming death/better nukes, wizzies got better nukes and have lures for pvp and most other classes can be very usefull in pvp.<br />
<br />
Now as far as Pve is concerned well if i didn't have a closeknit group of friends in EQ then i would prolly never get groups. Pre god i was hella sought out and never i mean never had a problem getting a group. Now every group wants 2 good healers ie cleric/cleric or cleric/druid an enchanter a warrior and a puller leaving very little room for me. I dunno our pve usefullness has dropped so much that i'm chomping on teh bit for WoW to come out so i can do something else. i just don't have it in me to lvl a new char and i refuse to ebay anything or use someone else char fulltime. hell i tried lvl'n a char again. made a monk just to play something drastically diff then a shaman and got him to 51. now he has like 3 elementals pieces waiting in the bank for him for 65 that he will prolly never hit and i have tons of stuff prolly 1million plat into him. ornate tunic. Ton po's staff fungi tons of other good droppable stuff but the XP grind is too much for me.<br />
<br />
I just want to feel usefull again and would love to see some of the stuff mentioned above adressed.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
