	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have a suggestion for a "new" and "improved" line for shamans in the spell/nuke category. <br />
<br />
<b>Disease Based <u>Nukes</u>.</b> <br />
<br />
We are shaman, afterall. We are witchdoctors. We can heal you or we can curse you. We know stuff about DISEASES. Keep our other spells the same, dots don't need to be altered. They manage to keep us effective in some of the older but as of yet not outdated content. Just give us something to make us useful in the NEW content.<br />
<br />
With Disease based nukes it NEEDS to be something with quick casting time. If I were a voodoo master, it would take nothing more than a mere pinprick to get the intended boils and sores to cover my target from head to toe. In fact, make THAT the spell message:<br />
<br />
<font face="fixedsys">So and so has inflicted %t with boils and sores.<br />
Your skin bubbles with infection.</font> <br />
<br />
Don't reduce the cast time on Poison Nukes even. It would take "time" for us to gather poisonous materials to conjure the spell. Disease is an altogether different thing. Make us masters of Disease in the nuke category. Make us keep that Malicious Decay spell memmed the same way we keep Turgur's memmed. Make me a scary thing for a mob to see, please. Make him worry about his pristine appearance.  <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="stick out tongue" smilieid="6" /><br />
<br />
Just to place this thought here as I read it by another poster elsewhere...I like the idea of rain based heals as an "upgrade" to our healing abilities. PC's out of the "range" of the healing rain would still be in peril. In fact, it might be "balanced" (thinking raid, here, where MA and his nearby compadres are the target for the cleansing showers) for the range to be close. Thus, the healing aggro would affect us and keep the peril a factor in gameplay.<br />
<br />
Just some thoughts.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
