<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Veril</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	Location: London, UK
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Another Issue at the High End with Focus - the overlaps that focus has compared to the equivalent Cleric and Druid buffs also cast focus in a poorer light by far that those comparable buffs.  <br />
<br />
Focus is incompatable with the Shielding Line that casters get.  This is in fact more significant than it first appears:<br />
<br />
Shield of Maelin:  350hp, 39AC, 40Magic Resistance.  <br />
Focus overwrites this giving 544HP.  This is a clear gain of 194hp for the 4 Int caster classes, but at the loss of the AC and Magic resistance.  The Druid and Clerics hit point buffs stack straight on top of the Int casters self buffs and provide 'full' increase.  <br />
<br />
However, Focus is also incompatable with the spell Shield of the Arcane (300hp, 36ac, 30MR), and this effect is on the Ornate Breastplate for Rogues, Berzerkers, Warriors and Monks (the pure melees).  In High End guilds it's not unreasonable to expect characters to have Ornate that they switch in for the clickety effects, or even wear full time.  Thus the value of Focus is dramatically reduced for these pure melees (the Str/dex on focus are irrelevent) compared to the equivalent Druid and Cleric Buffs.  Focus providing only +244hp at the cost of Magic Resistance and Armour Class - clearly not a zero sum gain.  I am not aware of equivalent armour that provides buffs for the melees that are incompatable with the symbol/virtue/9th lines.  <br />
<br />
Focus is also incompatable with the Cleric Self only buffs (admittedly on raids this doesn not apply as they will be using 9th instead).  The Cleric's incompatable buff provides Mana Regen and AC, and thus will be perfered to focus in most XP group circumstance.  <br />
<br />
Focus is also incompatable with some ranger buffs as well - but I'm not up on what rangers can do. <br />
<br />
In terms of buffing at the high end, the shaman clearly brings far less than the Druid or Cleric.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Veril: Dark Templars Prophet on Xegony</div>
	
	
