<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Ramhorn</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Stat buffs really become more useless, because of all the higher-end pieces of gear having +20 to 30 to each stat.  That adds up fast with the stat caps.  Gear in GoD is the same way. <br />
<br />
I see this as more of an issue than the stat caps itself.  If SOE would rather have players be more dependent on gear for stat increases than buffs, then they shouldn't bog us down with so many stat buffs and give us something more useful in its place.<br />
<br />
Long, long ago, disesase dots were increased to 2 minutes because that combined with poison was deemed too powerful.  Times have changed with the speedy DPS life EQ is now.  Lower disease dots down to poison, and increase the amount per tick.  If nuking isn't our thing, can even go farther into suggesting having 15 or 20 second dots doing large ticks of damage (750-1k).</p>
	
	
	
