	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This is a wonderful summary of the problems that have evolved in the shaman class.  It's important for SOE to understand our game experience, and this summary methodically examines each of our concerns with examples of in-game scenarios and the numbers behind them.  It offers no solutions, which in all honesty isn't our job.  We, the customers, have these problems with our service.  It is up to our service provider to find an equitable and fair solution.  We've helped by offering suggestions in other threads, but this summary defines the problem space for SOE and gives them the opportunity to walk inside the skin of a shaman from the player perspective.  This is exactly the kind of information SOE needs to enable them to understand why we as a class are unhappy.  It's useless to debate why this perspective seems to have escaped them up to this point; this summary offers a baseline from which to move forward.  veeshanMurtak took the time and skull-sweat to compile a valuable problem analysis for SOE -- let's hope they make full use of it.<br />
<br />
<br />
*edit to correct VM's name</p>
	
	
	
