	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Tugela</b><br /><i>You need to include hp regen in the mana regen calculations. That would vary depending on what race you are and what gear you have. I assume that most shaman keep replenishment up at all times of course.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I do not - it is not worth the hassle of memming it and certainly not worth a buff slot. The additional mana gained would be minimal anyways - replenishing our HPs after cannibalizing is close to free already.<br />
<br />
Rough numbers: replenishment saves a trushar every 6 minutes, that is a single canna every 6 minutes or 1.3 mana per tick.<br />
<br />
That is if you are never, not once, at full health. Real world numbers will be closer to 0.1 mana per tick.</p>
	
	
	
