	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Tugela</b><br /><i>Hmmm...with replen I'm regenning 46hp/tick, or 460hp/min, 1380hp/3minute, in other words it takes care of ~70% of each AA canni. With regen focus effects it would be more. That isnt insignificant, particularly if you are in combat and want to conserve mana or cant spare the time to Q. I'm seldom at full health if my mana bar isnt full, so it works in down time as well.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>That is not replenishment, that is replenishment + natural regen. Even counting your natural regeneration this saves you around 200 mana every 3 minutes (and costs 275 every 13.9 minutes).<br />
A gain of 85 mana(after focuses) every minute, if you are an iksar and make sure to never be at full health.<br />
That will up potential mana regeneration in my scenariois from 174/tick to 182/tick. Of course now I would have to account for the druid using replenishment for healing. Oh, and that reverse damage shield that clerics get.<br />
<br />
Bottom line: I already made a huge assumption in that my hypothetical shaman never overheals himself with Trushar. I made another huge assumption in having that shaman find something useful to cast between cannibalize IV refreshs. I am not going to add an even more hypothetical replenishment and I am certainly not going to account for iksar racial regeneration. Trushar is close to free as is anyways.</p>
	
	
	
